brewery.brewery_description: Legend Brewing Company is a commercial microbrewery providing true premium beers to many of the best pubs and restaurants in Richmond and other areas of Virginia since January, 1994. Our mission is to bring to our customers the finest and freshest brews as flavorful alternatives to mass-marketed mainstream products. We're one of the few craft breweries in this region producing both lagers and ales, which require different yeasts and maturation conditions. All Legend beers are unpasteurized and made from only two-row and specialty barley malt, hops, water and yeast.

beer.beer_description: A full bodied version of a British Brown Ale. Expect a rich, malt-foreward brew with a beautiful mahogony tone. Generous amounts of specialty malts bring flavors of sweet caramel, toasted nuts, coffee, and molasses, all perfectly balanced by a steady but cautious hop dryness. Fruity undertones provided by our house yeast strain bring the final flavor element to round out this world class ale.

Generous amounts of specialty malts bring flavors of sweet caramel, toasted nuts, coffee, and molasses, all perfectly balanced by a steady but cautious hop dryness. In the image of an English IPA, Legend Golden is a big, full-bodied brew with the perfect balance between malty sweetness and hop bitterness. Years ago, as an experimental brew, this underdog of a beer found its way into the hearts of Legend patrons and became a cult classic in Richmond. Legend Golden has been described as a "high class malt liquor" by a notable source. This strong ale sports a rich gold color, an aroma of sweet malt and clean hops, and an earthy, fruity flavor.
German-style beer with clean, crisp taste, a light bitterness and a pleasant hop aroma, medium body and pale color, offering far more character and flavor than typical American lager-style products.

Get ready for a winterized version of a classic Belgian Witbier (white beer). Legend Winter White starts with a blend of Belgian malts and wheat in the mash for a rich, sweet body and tangy crispness. Spicy hops blend in the boil with coriander and orange peel. During fermentation these flavors combine harmonically with a Belgian Trappist yeast strain (banana, pear bubblegum). The creamy mouthfeel of this unique unfiltered winter warmer pairs well with salads, seafood, poultry and pork dishes.

This pale-gold ale sports a light body and a clean malt flavor. Refreshing and quenching, Z Dam evokes an acute zestiness driven by a balance of late kettle hops and the addition of ginger, orange, and lime in the boil. Our Z Dam Ale is perfect to enjoy while basking in the sun on your patio, or when toasting a successful descent through the rapids of the mighty James River.

We've joined forces with a local distiller of fine spirits to bring you a rich and bold experience. We've taken our Legend Brown Ale and allowed it to mature in the oak bourbon barrels of the A. Smith Bowman Distillery for six weeks. A layer of boozy heat counters the richness and a dry finish calls for a re-load!

To celebrate our Anniversary and pay tribute to our Brown Ale, every year we brewed a bolder and robust version of the Legend Brown. The imperial version has an even fuller body, stronger malt flavors, and an added hop character. Seven types of barley malt yield a deep, rich body evoking biscuit, caramel, chocolate and coffee flavors. Our house ale yeast adds a level of fruity esters, and a moderate hop bite combines with alcohol warmth for a balanced finish.

Rich, roasty and loaded with chocolate and coffee flavors. Healthy amounts of specialty malts including caramel malt and roasted barley make this sweet black ale robust and full bodied. Hopping is minimal and for balance only. This beer is an excellent pair to most any meal, especially meat dishes and desserts.

Five months of aging brings the soft smoothness of natural carbonation and allows this sweet, complex brew to dry out considerably. The result is a “sipping beer” that doesn’t seem like one. The light, dry palate, combined with quenching qualities such as citrus and spice notes can lead one to get in a little too deep. Fermentation is on a Belgian Abbey style yeast strain which imparts interesting combinations of fruit and spice, as well as a faint bubble gum quality.

Legend Bohemian style Pilsner starts with a rich gold color and a firm malt background. A substantial body yields to a finish that is dry and crisp. Floral/spicy hop flavors are evident throughout. This beer is a bit of a more aggressive version of our Lager, still smooth and malty, but stronger and packing a bit more of a hop bite. 6.0% abv.

Rich, roasty and loaded with chocolate and coffee flavors. Healthy amounts of specialty malts including caramel malt and roasted barley make this sweet black ale robust and full bodied. Hopping is minimal and for balance only. This beer is an excellent pair to most any meal, especially meat dishes and desserts.

his beer's unusual name comes from the German "weiss" (wheat), and "hefe" (yeast). Therefore, a hefeweizen is an unfiltered wheat beer. Weizen beers are something of an anomaly among German beers, as they are fermented on ale yeast whereas virtually all other beers from this country are lagers.The yeast strain dominates the aroma and flavor profile in this brew. If you suspect we added banana and clove to the beer, you are simply picking up qualities of this wonderful yeast. Our Hefeweizen is mashed with a 50/50 blend of wheat malt and barley malt. The wheat portion of the mash is responsible for keeping the flavor crisp and the body light. Hallertau and Sterling hops are used minimally for balance and another dimension of spice. Expect an intense aroma of fruit (banana, apricot, citrus), and spice (clove, pepper). The initial flavor is sharp and tart, yeilding to a malty sweetness in the middle. The finish is effervescent, dry, and quenching. Legend Hefeweizen is the perfect match for light summer fare including salads, seafood, and grilled meats. Available on draft and in 12 oz. bottles all summer. 5% Alc. By Vol.

Legend Hopfest originated in 2005 as a one-off seasonal beer. Hopfest was brewed to celebrate Legend’s eleventh year of brewing craft beer (we called it micro-brew back then)! Expect a deep golden colored beer with a distinct pine/fruit hop character. This sturdy and balanced IPA layers Amarillo, Simcoe, and Citra hops on top of a sturdy specialty malt background. An additional week of post fermentation dry-hopping yields a juicy aroma. Finding the elusive balance between flavor intensity and approachability, Legend Hopfest IPA has earned a spot as one of the “brewer’s favorites.” We hope you enjoy it as much as we do!
